## Microsoft Writing Style Guide â€“ One-Page Summary

### Purpose

The Microsoft Writing Style Guide provides guidance for writing about computer technology, ensuring content is clear, concise, and accessible to a global audience. [Microsoft Learn](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/style-guide/welcome/?utm_source=chatgpt.com)

------

### Core Principles

- Clarity and Simplicity: Use straightforward language and simple sentence structures to make content easily understandable. [Microsoft Learn+4Microsoft Learn+4Microsoft Learn+4](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/style-guide/global-communications/writing-tips?utm_source=chatgpt.com)
- Inclusive Language: Employ bias-free language that respects all readers, avoiding idioms and culture-specific references. [Microsoft Learn+1Microsoft Learn+1](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/style-guide/global-communications/writing-tips?utm_source=chatgpt.com)
- Global Readiness: Write content that is easily localizable by using clear terms and avoiding region-specific expressions. [Microsoft Learn](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/style-guide/global-communications/writing-tips?utm_source=chatgpt.com)
- Accessibility: Structure content to be accessible to all users, including those using assistive technologies. 

------

### Writing Style

- Tone: Adopt a warm, relaxed, and helpful tone.[Microsoft Learn](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/style-guide/welcome/?utm_source=chatgpt.com)
- Voice: Use active voice and second-person pronouns ("you") to engage readers directly. 
- Conciseness: Be succinct; remove unnecessary words and focus on essential information. 

------

### Formatting Guidelines

- Headings: Use sentence-style capitalization (capitalize only the first word and proper nouns). [Microsoft Learn+1Microsoft Learn+1](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/style-guide/global-communications/writing-tips?utm_source=chatgpt.com)
- Lists: Use bulleted lists for non-sequential items and numbered lists for step-by-step instructions. Do not use bold. [Microsoft Learn](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/style-guide/scannable-content/lists?utm_source=chatgpt.com)
- UI Elements: When referring to user interface elements, use bold formatting for labels and match the UI text exactly. [Microsoft Learn](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/style-guide/procedures-instructions/formatting-text-in-instructions?utm_source=chatgpt.com)

------

### Writing Procedures

- Step-by-Step Instructions:
  - Use numbered lists for procedures.
  - Begin each step with an imperative verb.
  - Keep steps concise and limit procedures to seven steps when possible. [Microsoft Learn+2Microsoft Learn+2Microsoft Learn+2](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/style-guide/procedures-instructions/formatting-text-in-instructions?utm_source=chatgpt.com)[Microsoft Learn](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/style-guide/procedures-instructions/writing-step-by-step-instructions?utm_source=chatgpt.com)
- Single-Step Instructions: Use bullet points for single actions.

------

### Accessibility Considerations

- People-First Language: Refer to individuals before their disabilities (e.g., "person with a disability").[Microsoft Learn](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/style-guide/accessibility/writing-all-abilities?utm_source=chatgpt.com)
- Clear Instructions: Provide straightforward and concise instructions, especially for accessibility features.[Microsoft Learn](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/style-guide/accessibility/writing-all-abilities?utm_source=chatgpt.com)
- Descriptive Links: Use meaningful link text that clearly describes the destination. 

------

### Code Examples

- Relevance: Ensure code examples are pertinent and demonstrate real-world scenarios.[Microsoft Learn](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/style-guide/developer-content/code-examples?utm_source=chatgpt.com)
- Clarity: Write code that is easy to read and understand, with appropriate comments.
- Reusability: Design code examples that developers can easily adapt for their own use. [Microsoft Learn](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/style-guide/developer-content/code-examples?utm_source=chatgpt.com)

------

For more detailed guidance, visit the full Microsoft Writing Style Guide: [Microsoft Learn](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/style-guide/welcome/?utm_source=chatgpt.com)
